Package burlap.oomdp.stochasticgames.agentactions

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    GroundedSGAgentAction
    A GroundedSGAgentAction is a high-level implementation of the AbstractGroundedAction that is closely associated with the SGAgentAction definition of actions that can be taken by agents in a multi-agent stochastic game.
    ObParamSGAgentAction
    If your SGAgentAction implementation is paramerterized to OO-MDP ObjectInstance references, you can subclass this SGAgentAction subclass to easily provide that functionality.
    ObParamSGAgentAction.GroundedObParamSGAgentAction  
    SGAgentAction
    An abstract class for providing action definitions that are selectable by agents (SGAgent) in a stochastic game.
    SimpleGroundedSGAgentAction
    A GroundedSGAgentAction implementation for actions that are parameter-less.
    SimpleSGAgentAction
    This SGAgentAction definition defines a parameter-less agent action that can be executed in every state.
